727985f-b.title: Queens: Shore Boulevard - 21st Avenue
727985f-b.text:
Shore Boulevard (foreground, not shown), east side, between Twenty-
first Ave. (left) and Ditmars Boulevard, showing in a set of four views
the Nesbitt house from 1859 to 1873. Also known as the Nesmith house.
Views 3 and 4 are rear views. In 1928 it occupied lot 202 in block 896.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

727984f-b.title: Queens: Shore Boulevard - 21st Avenue
727984f-b.text:
(1)
Shore Boulevard (right), south of 2lst Ave., showing in the back-
ground (right) the former home of A. D. Ditmar and beyond it the New
York Connecting Railroad Bridge. In the foreground is the Nesbit house.
April 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(2)
The same, viewed from 2lst Ave. This bridge was designed by
Gustave Lindenthal and opened on April 1, 1917. The cost was over
~12,000,000. The steel arches rise 220 feet and have a clear span be-
tween abutments of about 1000 feet.
June 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

725115f-a.title: Queens: 21st Avenue - Shore Boulevard
725115f-a.text:
21st Avenue, adjoining the N. E. corner of Shore Boulevwrd,
showing the house which belonged to Polhemus in 1873. The
view is forth from Shore Boulevard across 21st Avenue, which
was formely known as Wolcott Avenue.
P. L. Sperr  Pebruary 9, 1932
NO REPRODUCTIONS

727982f-b.title: Queens: Shore Boulevard - 21st Avenue
727982f-b.text:
(1)
Shore Boulevard, north from 21st Ave., showing in the foreground
(partially seen) the home of Abraham Polhemus; in the background is
that of Jerome S. Polhemus.
April 1925.
Eugene L. Ambruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(2)
The same, showing a close up of A. Polhemus' farmhouse, and a
gas tank of the Consolidated Gas Company upon whose land the house
now stands. Note,history has it that Richard Berrien bought in
1737 the land with a house thereon. Jacob Rapelje the next owner
built the present home.
March 1923.
Eugene L. Ambruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(3)
The same, a slightly different angle.
April 1925.
Eugene L. Ambruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(4)
Thhe same, another angle.
June 1925.
Eugene L. Ambruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
